 period within 10 days. The\nradial rotational gradient between the surface and core is found to be\n6.9+2.0/-1.0. The agreement between the surface rotation with the seismic\nresult indicates that the full convective envelope is rotating quasi-rigidly.\nThe models of the lithium abundance are compatible with a rigid rotation in the\nradiative zone during the main sequence. Because of the many constraints\noffered by oscillating stars in binary systems, such objects are important test\nbeds of stellar evolution.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 14 Dec 2017 13:03:53 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sat, 13 Jan 2018 19:03:00 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-05-02"}
